criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age between 18-80 years;

          -  BMI 25-40;

          -  Fatty liver disease (bright liver, hepatomegaly by ultrasound (Liver span > 15 cm mid
             clavicle line), splenomegaly (>13 cm) or both.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Alcohol abuse>30 gm/day, or > 70 gram per week;

          -  Soft drink abuse;

          -  Drugs known to cause fatty liver;

          -  Chronic hepatitis (B and C);

          -  Biliary liver disease;

          -  Autoimmune hepatitis;

          -  HIV;

          -  Genetic/Metabolic liver disease (Wilson, alpha-1 antitrypsin, CF);

          -  Failure to give informed consent
